# Claude Code sync

Always consdifer ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md as a source of all global instructions and guidelines.

Agent definitions live in `~/.claude/agents/` (also linked as `~/.cursor/agents/`). Skills live in `~/.claude/skills/`. When editing agents or global policy, change Claude Code sources; Cursor reuses them.

Try your best to avoid duplicating code. Explore adjacent files, project files, use the Depagent tool, and code search. Don't hesitate break existing functions and classes into pieces to move common code parts into separate common abstractions.
Do not add obvious or trivial comments. Prefer code expressiveness, readability and clarity over comments.
Ask deepagent tool about arcadia code projects and yandex-specific (or unknown) infrastructure. If you see an unknown term, first thing to do is to refer to deepagent tool, not code exploring. Ask deepagent tool about best implementations practices when in doubt. Deepagent tool provides best results when asked in Russian.
Use `~/.venv` virtualenv to run python.
Use Yandex's version control system which is "arc".

## Memory and self-improvement

Delegate to subagents (see `~/.claude/agents/`):

- **memory** — `~/.claude/memory/`, start at INDEX.md.
- **self-improvement** — agents, CLAUDE.md, `~/claude-agent-instructions/`.

**Mandatory:** on any substantive user correction or feedback about agent behavior (not bare «ok»/«thanks»), the parent agent must run **self-improvement** via Task in the same turn, with user quote + what was done + proposed instruction fixes. See `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` § «Обязательный self-improvement».

- **manager** — coordinate agents; on difficulty (blocker, plan drift, stuck subtask) delegate to manager; ensure self-improvement runs on user feedback.

## Agents (Task / subagents)

On **difficulty** (blocker, repeated failure, plan mismatch, unclear next step — base task or auxiliary subtask), delegate **manager** (`Task`, `subagent_type: manager`). See `~/.claude/agents/manager.md`.

Delegate via the Task tool using `subagent_type` equal to the agent `name` from `~/.claude/agents/*.md`:

- **manager** — multi-step tasks, overcoming difficulties (investigate → critique → replan → act), session review, agent routing and resource plans.
- **planner** — Tracker tickets and detailed implementation plans.
- **thinker** — verify reasoning on non-trivial or ambiguous work.
- **memory** — save or retrieve domain facts in `~/.claude/memory/`.
- **self-improvement** — user corrections, systemic improvements, instruction repo.
- **logos-*** agents ONLY when the task is directly related to the Logos ETL system.
- **yandex-developer** for general Yandex/Arcadia development; may delegate to planner, thinker, memory, manager.

When the user says "ask deepagent" or "consult deepagent", use the deepagent MCP tool (`depagent-generate_answer` / `mcp__yandex__deepagent-generate_answer`), not a subagent.
